latestPosts.caption:
#GraziaBeauty 2024 was a year of bold creativity, blending nostalgia with audacious experimentation. From heavy blushes and dark ombre lips to bleached brows, gemstones, and graphic liners, make-up trends moved beyond clean-girl monotony to embrace individuality and flair. Celebrating this shift, six beauty creators reimagined the year’s standout looks with their unique spins. Rahil kicks things off with his take on Brat Beauty, a sassy, unapologetic aesthetic that demands attention.

When Charli XCX dropped her studio album Brat, it not only took over the cultural zeitgeist but also inspired an aesthetic of its own. Soon, the signature neon green shade found its way into make-up as Brat Beauty. Positioned as the antithesis of clean-girl make-up, this messy, carefree trend—with no rules and plenty of sass—dominated the summer of 2024.

Words: Konika Datta
Photograph: Yusuf Lokhandwala
Make-up: Saikat Chakraborty, National Artist, M.A.C Cosmetics India 
Hair: Shimchuila Mungkung (Ashim) and Nikesh Sharma, Looks Salon
